The Minister of Youth, Sports and Development, Sunday Dare said on Friday that Nigeria would soon set up a robotics laboratory in Abuja. Dare, who made this known in a tweet, said the Ministry of Youth and Sports Development is working in collaboration with the Federal government to set up a robotics laboratory in Abuja. He said setting up of a robotics laboratory to engage and create opportunities for youths in the country. “With Silas Adekunle, leading Robotics Engineeer in Lagos on Thursday. In collaboration with the Ministry of Youth & Sports Development, Nigeria is set to have a robotics laboratory in Abuja that will engage our Youth”, he said.